The African Women Conference, an international women’s organization, has congratulated FCT Minister of State, Dr. Ramatu Tijjani Aliyu, on receiving a Doctorate (PhD) Degree from Nasarawa State University, Keffi (NSUK). In a statement issued in Abuja by its Chief Operations Officer, Mrs. Funmi Ajare, the organisation praised the award as an incredible achievement and a testimonial to the minister’s intellectual sagacity and self-confidence over the years. The statement urged the minister to use her achievements to ensure that women are at the forefront of driving Africa’s economic progress, as well as to work toward a gender and social inclusion policy agenda that protects women and female children in diverse countries. The statement reads in part: “This amazing accomplishment is just one step on your journey. Your ability to relentlessly search for solutions to problems and find innovative ways to improve the world, is the key to this success and many to come. “We know you overcome so many obstacles to achieve this success story. Your perseverance is an inspiration to many African women, and you deserved all the laurels coming your way. “We noticed that as you worked toward this academic success, you behaved with such humility, grace and kindness to others. We appreciate how you always share your success with your team, and your love for your members is one of the reasons you rise to the top. Congratulations!”